  "body": "### Description\n\nResponse when invalid endpoint is called be agent responsive, when calling an endpoint that doesn't exists, Quarkus returns a big HTML page with the current available endpoints which is great, but if you are curling you get a lot of HTML code that is hard to follow\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nThe idea would be make things agent aware, so if you detect it is a real browser then show that HTML page, but if it is curl/wget/ or any other property that shows it is a terminal, then switch to a text version.",
